{"name": "onkeypress", "metadata": {"name": "onkeypress", "version": "0.0.3", "classifiers": ["License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3"], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["toggle-cbreak"], "summary": "A simple program that allows users to make their terminal reactive to keypresses", "upload_time": 1733836727}, "documentation": ["\n# onkeypress\n\nAllows users to make terminal react to keypresses\n\n# installation\n\n```\npip install onkeypress\n```\n\n# quickstart\n\n```python\nfrom onkeypress import while_not_exit, onkeypress, Key\n\ndef func(key):\n    print(f\"{key} was pressed\")\n\nwhile_not_exit(\n    onkeypress(Key.UP).invoke(func, [\"up\"]),\n    onkeypress(Key.DOWN).invoke(func, [\"down\"]),\n    onkeypress(\"a\").invoke(func, [\"a!!\"]),\n    onkeypress(\"s\").invoke(func, [\"s!!\"]),\n    exit_key=Key.ENTER,\n)\n```\n\n^ after running this, your terminal now waits for your keypresses\n- if you hit ArrowUp, it prints \"up was pressed\"\n- if you hit ArrowDown, it prints \"down was pressed\"\n- if you hit \"a\", it prints \"a was pressed\"\n- if you hit \"s\", it prints \"s was pressed\"\n- if you hit Enter, this function ends\n"], "modules": [{"name": "onkeypress.decorators", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "onkeypress.decorators.handle_cbreak_and_exceptions", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "function", "type": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "Callable", "xref": {"fqname": "typing.Callable", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["At start of function, turn on cbreak mode\nAt the end, always turn off cbreak mode"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "onkeypress", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "onkeypress.onkeypress", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"